@startuml StateReminder
title Reminder Lifecycle — State Diagram

skinparam stateFontSize 12

[*] --> Created : new Reminder()

state Created {
    Created : Entry / validate() is called
    Created : Entry / priority is assigned
}

Created --> Scheduled : save() to repository\n[validation passed]

state Scheduled {
    Scheduled : Entry / scheduledTime is set
    Scheduled : Do / waiting for scheduled time
}

Scheduled --> TimeCheck : timer tick

state TimeCheck <<choice>>

TimeCheck --> DueSoon : [scheduledTime - now() < 1 hour]
TimeCheck --> Scheduled : [scheduledTime - now() >= 1 hour]
TimeCheck --> Overdue : [scheduledTime < now()]

state DueSoon #FFFFAA {
    DueSoon : Entry / EventManager.notify(REMINDER_DUE_SOON)
    DueSoon : Do / highlighted in yellow in UI
}

DueSoon --> Overdue : scheduledTime has passed
DueSoon --> Completed : markCompleted()\n[user marks as done]
DueSoon --> Deleted : deleteReminder(id)

Scheduled --> Completed : markCompleted()\n[user marks as done]
Scheduled --> Updated : updateReminder()\n[user edits fields]

state Overdue #FFcccc {
    Overdue : Entry / EventManager.notify(REMINDER_OVERDUE)
    Overdue : Do / highlighted in red in UI
}

Overdue --> Completed : markCompleted()
Overdue --> Updated : updateReminder()\n[reschedule to new time]

state Updated {
    Updated : Entry / new scheduledTime set
    Updated : Entry / repository.update()
}

Updated --> Scheduled : validation passed\n[new scheduledTime in future]
Updated --> Overdue : [new scheduledTime still past]

state Completed #ccFFcc {
    Completed : Entry / setCompleted(true)
    Completed : Entry / EventManager.notify(REMINDER_COMPLETED)
    Completed : Entry / observers refresh panels
}

Completed --> Deleted : deleteReminder(id)

state Deleted #cccccc {
    Deleted : Entry / repository.delete(id)
    Deleted : Entry / EventManager.notify(REMINDER_DELETED)
}

Deleted --> [*]

note right of TimeCheck
  **Time-based state transitions:**
  The system periodically checks
  scheduledTime against current time
  to determine state transitions.
end note

note left of Created
  **5 Reminder Subtypes & validate() rules:**
  - FeedingReminder: foodType required, portionGrams > 0
  - MedicationReminder: medicationName required, dosage > 0
  - VetAppointment: clinicName required, estimatedCost >= 0
  - GroomingReminder: groomingType required
  - ExerciseReminder: exerciseType required, durationMinutes > 0
end note

note bottom of Scheduled
  **Observer Pattern:**
  Every state transition triggers
  EventManager.notify() to update
  DashboardPanel & RemindersPanel.
end note

@enduml
